The paper discusses a decoding algorithm and architecture for polar codes, which are commonly used in information theory and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves hardware implementation, which suggests categories such as cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.ET (Embedded Systems). The algorithm involves tree traversal and optimization, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes a decoder architecture for use in communication systems, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
